# Immersive Commons — agent rules

This is the public skills + SDK repo for the Immersive Commons agent API
(https://www.immersivecommons.com — Floor 10, Frontier Tower SF).

- Read `AGENTS.md` first: it is the sourced API contract. Machine-readable
  docs on the live site (`/.well-known/mcp.json`, `/.well-known/ai-agent.json`,
  `/openapi.json`, `/llms.txt`) always win over repo prose.
- Prefer MCP: `https://www.immersivecommons.com/api/mcp` (Streamable HTTP).
  10 tools are public — smoke-test with `ic_signal_get_latest`. REST and
  A2A (`/api/a2a`) expose the same capabilities behind the same token.
- Never invent endpoints, tool names, or scopes; the catalog in
  `/.well-known/mcp.json` is exhaustive.
- Auth is a per-user `agt_*` bearer minted via the human-approved
  device-code flow (`https://www.immersivecommons.com/auth.md`). Agents
  cannot and must not self-mint.
- Skills follow the `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` layout with `name` +
  `description` YAML frontmatter; keep that contract when editing.
- Live-API writes (RSVPs, submissions, bookings, sends) are consequential —
  get human confirmation before firing them.
